  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Water and Sanitation Facilities for Undocumented Returnees and IDPs in Laghman Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">175 kits distributed across 3 communities
4 new water wells will be drilled and equeped with hand pumps
4 new latrines and 4 bathing facilities will be constracted 
10 existing water wells will be chlorinated.
The 100% or 175 families of beneficiaries will attend awareness session on personal and environmental hygiene.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The most vulnerable 175 families will have access to adequate and secure water for drinking porpose and will have access to safe sanitary latrines and bathing facilities which will ensure protection from diseases as well as avert related impacts on health, dignity and well-being. The hygiene kits will help them in improvement in their life conditions through access to required tools and instruments. The support provided to the target families will help them in rehabilitation and will enable them to save money they will be spending on hygiene kits. The money saved will help them to cope with other families needs especially during the winter season. The impact will be observed immediately after the distribution of the items and will be long lasting. 
The awareness raising on hygiene practices will enable female family members of the returnees to take care of their personal and family hygiene.</narrative>
  </description>
